{
  "text": "Similarly, reports were also found with regard to highly virulent R. solanacearum strains UW120 and UW276 which are found in Mexico, USA and Kenya in solanaceous plant [CITATION_1] . The results obtained from the present studies correlates previous reports in amplifying R. solanacearum isolates from Indian origin using endoglucanase region and confirms the presence of R. solanacearum in India [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] .",
  "correct_citation": {
